atlas.controller

Class CategoryController

  • java.lang.Object
    • atlas.controller.BasicController
      • atlas.controller.CategoryController
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    @ViewScoped
 @Named(value="categoryController")
public class CategoryController
extends BasicController
implements Serializable
    Provides content for browsing categories. ViewScoped managed bean, controller for category.xhtml component. Should be initialized by calling the init() method.
    Author:
    Michal Smrha

    • Method Detail

      • init

        public void init()
        Initializes current Category based on bound "categoryId". Creates localized views of current Category, its subcategories and pages. Also creates views of root categories.

      • addNewPage

        public String addNewPage(boolean ajax)
        Creates new blank page in current category and sets FacesMessage. Checks if editor is logged. If this check fails, nothing is created and warning is set. If all checks pass, page is created and info is set.
        Parameters:
        ajax - True if called by ajax, false if refresh is needed.
        Returns:
        Redirection string, null if ajax.

      • deletePage

        public String deletePage(int pageId,
                         boolean ajax)
        Deletes Page entity of matching ID. Checks if editor is logged. If this check fails, nothing is deleted and warning is set. If all checks pass, page is deleted and info is set.
        Parameters:
        pageId - ID of the page to be deleted.
        ajax - True if called by ajax, false if refresh is needed.
        Returns:
        Redirection string, null if ajax.

      • goEditPage

        public String goEditPage(int pageId)
        Redirects to page editor of a page with matching ID. Checks if editor is logged. If this check fails, redirect is null. If all checks pass, redirect points to editor.
        Parameters:
        pageId - ID of page to edit.
        Returns:
        Redirection string.

      • getCurrentCategory

        public CategoryView getCurrentCategory()
        Gets currentCategory, which contains basic localized information about current category in the form of CategoryView.
        Returns:
        Currently active category. Default info if current entity is null.

      • getChildCategories

        public List<CategoryView> getChildCategories()
        Gets childCategories, which contains basic localized information about subcategories of current category in the form of a list of CategoryViews.
        Returns:
        List of subcategories of currently active category. Empty list if current entity is null.

      • getRootCategories

        public List<CategoryView> getRootCategories()
        Gets rootCategories, which contains basic localized information about top level categories (categories without a parent) in the form of a list of CategoryViews.
        Returns:
        List of top level categories. Empty list if current entity is null.

      • getPages

        public List<PageView> getPages()
        Gets "pages", which contains basic localized information about pages directly nested in current category in the form of a list of PageViews.
        Returns:
        List of pages in active category. Empty list if current entity is null.

      • getCategoryId

        public int getCategoryId()
        Returns:
        ID of currently active category.

      • setCategoryId

        public void setCategoryId(int categoryId)
        Parameters:
        categoryId - ID of currently active category.
